## Conjecture (CPRR)
- Hypothesis 1: Splitting the docs into a release-notes file
  (RELEASE-0.6.0.org), a canonical reference (TELEMETRY.org), and
  inline .env.template comments gives us three layers a user can
  consult independently. Release notes are read once. The reference
  is read for ongoing operations. The .env.template is read when
  setting up a new box.
- Hypothesis 2: The model-selection rationale (>=3B params for
  reliable tool calling) is non-obvious enough that future users
  will hit the same surprise unless we document it.

